The paper deals with the complexity of model checking for recursion schemes, which is a topic related to logic and automata theory. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the modal mu-calculus, which is a formalism used in verification and model checking, making cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with the complexity of acceptance problems for alternating parity tree automata, which is a topic related to computational complexity, making cs.PL (Computational Complexity) a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the resource usage verification of functional programs, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the complexity of acceptance problems for disjunctive transition functions, which is a topic related to concurrency and parallelism, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) another possible sub-category.
